content: The app is awesome & the support phenomenal. I had an issue w/ the app & the developer fixed it & had an update ready in less than a day. As a regular Steel Challenge competitor I can honestly say this app has helped me improve. Being a data driven person, the integration w/ the AMG timer has allowed me to see, analyze and tailor my practice to improve my transition times a/f seeing the splits from my match performances. This app has paid for itself many times over in terms of my progress.
Outstanding app for viewing , comparing and performing what if analysis of scoring for various shooting competitions
excellent
Excellent.
Match performance analysis and much more. When paired with a AMG timer the details are amazing.

One of the beauties of this app is its ability to take post match depression to new levels via the "what IF I hadn't Miked it up all day" feature. Seriously though... I do enjoy the app for digging into each stage and being able to more definitively recall performances.

content: The PractiScore Competitor app saves a LOT of time for me!  I consider myself a fairly serious USPSA shooter and used to do a lot of napkin and spreadsheet "what if" scenarios after the results came out for a match that I shot.    With this app, researching "what if" is now easy and intuitive!  I can test out where I would have placed if I didn't have "that mulfunction", "that unnecessary reload", "if that mike was a charlie", etc.  Comparison with other shooters in the same division, different divisions, or just comparing my own scores from a morning and afternoon run at the same match is instant.  Along with the Shot Coach app (which, sadly, isn't available for any devices except iOS devices), this is one of the two most valuable post-match analysis tools that I have available!
Love it!
Best scoring app ever!! If you love the sport, you'll love this app.
I just search for my USPSA number and get the results then add others to compare. Love it!

LOVE this app and what it does, the search by name/number/match feature is awesome when it works. The ability to edit your scores for "theoretical outcomes" is a thing of beauty. That said, while I'm slowly getting used to it, I still find the app very counter-intuitive and difficult to use. For example: to search for a match I have to undo all my match edits (even if I didn't make any, to go back to the original overall results), go to "change match", "search", and then "my first match" - which makes no sense to me and it took me a while to figure out. Especially irritating and unusual (for a droid) is the fact that the "back" button closes the app, instead of just taking you back to the previous screen. Other than being in desperate need of a UI overhaul (the sole reason for only 3 stars) this app has provided an answer to a lot of wants, needs, and "wouldn't it be cool if..."'s. Great job guys! Can't wait to see how it improves!
replyContent: Lorna, the "Match Search" action is available from the main menu. See 3 vertical dots at the top right corner. On the same menu you also have option to switch between matches without undoing changes.
